It is possible that the open-label nature of the study might have introduced information bias or influenced provider behavior.

limitations_and_caveats:
Due to the off-label use of HCQ, we were not able to incorporate randomization in our design.
The outcome of CLI was based on self-reported symptoms, which is prone to bias.
The trial may be under-powered as recruitment was forced to stop early at 221 instead of 360 because of the demand for and subsequent shortage of HCQ in March 2020.
Our study participants were young and healthy compared to other prophylaxis trials, which may partially explain the low rates of COVID-19.
